      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:1:1:16",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) إِنَّ قُلُوبَ الْجُهَّالِ تَسْتَفِزُّهَا الْأَطْمَاعُ وَ تَرْتَهِنُهَا الْمُنَى وَ تَسْتَعْلِقُهَا الْخَدَائِعُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Muhammad, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Ja’far<sup>asws</sup>, from his<sup>asws</sup> father<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The hearts of the ignorant ones trigger the greed, and the yearnings hold them hostage, and the deceptions attach to them’."
        ]
      }
    }
